  ./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:135:**2. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json`** — one per supported artifact, schema [metadata-library-index-schema-v2.0.1.json](../metadata/schemas/metadata-library-index-schema-v2.0.1.json). It is a JSON **array** of entries; each entry's required fields are `metadata-version`, `tested-versions`, and `allowed-packages`, with optional `default-for` (Java regex), `latest: true`, `override: true`, `requires: ["<group>:<artifact>", …]`, `test-version`, `skipped-versions`, `language`, and the four URL fields. Plugin-relevant fields are the first six.
  ./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:139:**3. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/reachability-metadata.json`** — the only file the plugin loads at native-image time. Schema [reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json](../metadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json) (a vendored copy of the upstream GraalVM schema), with top-level keys `reflection`, `jni`, `resources`, `bundles`, `serialization`, and `foreignCalls`. Every entry must carry a `condition.typeReachable` clause (FR-M-2) so the plugin can rely on conditional registration. The legacy split-config layout (`reflect-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, …) is no longer present.
  ./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:143:1. `v ∈ tested-versions` → use that entry's `metadata-version` directory directly.
  ./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:151:    LoadIndex --> Tested{"Any entry with<br/><code>v ∈ tested-versions</code>?"}
  ./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:152:    Tested -- yes --> UseTested["Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>"]
  ./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:154:    DefaultFor -- yes --> UseDefault["Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>"]
  ./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:158:    Latest -- yes --> UseLatest["Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>"]
  ./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:180:- **FR-M-6** Exactly one entry in a non-empty `index.json` must carry `latest: true`. If a library version is not in `tested-versions`, the harness selects an entry by matching the optional `default-for` regex.
  ./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:190:- **FR-T-6** Newly added `tested-versions` entries are recorded in `index.json` only after they pass on **every** required environment (enforced by `verify-new-library-version-compatibility`).
